      "text": "In the analysis of multivariate observations designed to assess subjects with respect to an attribute, a Guttman scale (named after [[Louis Guttman]]) is a single (unidimensional) ordinal scale for the assessment of the attribute, from which the original observations may be reproduced. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guttman_scale wikipedia]"
    },
